From: Daniel Nylander <daniel@danielnylander.se>
Subject: [PATCH] DRASCULA: Fix sscanf buffer overflow in resource loading

sscanf(buf, "%s", result) writes unlimited data into the destination
buffer. If the input file contains a long string, this overwrites
adjacent memory — a classic buffer overflow exploitable via crafted
save files or game data.

Replace with width-limited format specifier.

---
 engines/drascula/resource.cpp | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/engines/drascula/resource.cpp b/engines/drascula/resource.cpp
index abcdef2..1234568 100644
--- a/engines/drascula/resource.cpp
+++ b/engines/drascula/resource.cpp
@@ -86,7 +86,7 @@ void DrasculaEngine::getStringFromLine(char *buf, int len, char *result) {
 	getLine(buf);
 
-	if (!sscanf(buf, "%s", result)) {
+	if (!sscanf(buf, "%255s", result)) {
 		*result = 0;
 	}
 }
